What are Timing Functions?
 Used to run code after some time or repeatedly


1. setTimeout()

    Runs code once after delay

    setTimeout(() => {
    console.log("Hello after 2 seconds");
    }, 2000);

    2000 = 2 seconds


2. setInterval()

    Runs code again and again after interval

    setInterval(() => {
    console.log("Running every 2 seconds");
    }, 2000);


3. clearTimeout()

 Stops setTimeout

    let id = setTimeout(() => {
    console.log("Will not run");
    }, 2000);

    clearTimeout(id);

        Example (Counter)

            let count = 0;

            let id = setInterval(() => {
            count++;
            console.log(count);

            if (count === 5) {
                clearInterval(id);
            }
            }, 1000);


Important Points

 `setTimeout` → runs once
 `setInterval` → runs repeatedly
 Time is in milliseconds
 Always store id if you want to stop

